nodes.text: A leviathan species lived on the coral moon Rugosa sometime before a calamity had boiled its oceans away. A skeleton remained on the moon during the time of the Clone Wars, allowing a school of neebrays to colonize the ribs.
Bones of the leviathan appeared in the 2020 short story "Sharing the Same Face", written by Jason Fry and published in the anthology The Clone Wars: Stories of Light and Dark.
